3D Model of the City of Adelaide,"3D Model of the city of Adelaide. The link contains a list of a large number of sub-folders and files. At the bottom of the list are the help files, block map and metadata. Some blocks have had their original origins reset, please refer to the 'How to fix broken origins' spreadsheet. *TIP for Sketch Up only* - bring the models in & attach them to the origin, set the scale to 39.625 (inches in 1 metre). Scale for all other software is 1:100. For quicker performance in the textured version, go to View Menu, Face Style and select 'shaded'.",dataset,aar,Creative Commons Attribution,active,Linked,never,/data/dataset/335b887e-58ad-42e0-902e-7ebf05515b87,2015-06-10T02:09:58.801909,2022-11-14T00:23:03.388288,city@adelaidecitycouncil.com,,2016,,Adelaide & North Adelaide,Local Government,data.sa.gov.au,City of Adelaide,"3d, 3d model, buildings, city, map",
Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander students by school type,"Full-time equivalent enrolments of Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander students by type of school, collected as part of the annual enrolment data collection in Term 3, from 2012.

Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander students – students who have identified to be of Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander origin. 

The term ‘origin’ is considered to relate to people’s Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander descent and for some, but not all, their cultural identify. 
