Hundreds,"The Hundreds layer is a data set that reflects the official boundaries of Hundreds in South Australia as defined by the Crown Land Management Act, 2009 or preceding Acts. Used in conjunction with cadastral boundaries to assist in the definition of land parcels.",dataset,aar,Creative Commons Attribution,active,Linked,daily,/data/dataset/9aae79ed-0b42-4db7-8441-9889a4e842d3,2016-03-23T23:07:44.140522,2024-07-16T06:00:19.189119,dhud.reception@sa.gov.au,Updated down to unit area,1993-02-01,Current,South Australia,South Australian Government,data.sa.gov.au,Department for Housing and Urban Development,"Counties, Hundreds, Sections",housing-land-planning-and-infrastructure
IbraSubregionAust70 CARRS Assessment,"Presents the results of two approaches to assessing CARRS (Comprehensive, Adequate, Representative Reserve System): a geographic approach and an outcomes approach.

The geographic approach calculates the proportion of protected areas within each IBRA (Interim Biogeographic Regionalisation of Australia v7) region and subregion to assess sufficiency and to set priorities for future protection and conservation. This is the traditional approach used for CARRS assessment in Australia and has been applied at the State scale (and is also applied nationally).

The outcome approach considers how irreplaceable each patch of habitat is, based on its contribution to the conservation of species (using vascular plants and vertebrates). All areas critical to the long-term conservation of one or more species of conservation concern are used to assess sufficiency and to set priorities for future protection and conservation. Due to data paucity, the current assessment was only able to encompass the agricultural zone of South Australia. Work has commenced that will enable the Statewide application of this approach, which will be captured in future updates.

This tabular output is designed to be joined to the LANDSCAPE.IbraSubregionAust70 spatial layer.",dataset,eng,Creative Commons Attribution,active,Linked,as required,/data/dataset/5b7b6d1d-afca-463c-bd2a-23fa704d05b3,2025-10-03T03:42:50.474141,2025-11-20T02:52:13.929492,robin.green@sa.gov.au,,11 June 2025,11 June 2025,SA0062407: South Australia,Government of South Australia,data.sa.gov.au,Department for Environment and Water,"CARRS, Comprehensive Adequate and Representative Reserve System, IBRA, Interim Biogeographic Regionalisation of Australia",government-reporting-and-policy
