Limestone Coast Local Health Network (LCLHN),"The Limestone Coast Local Health Network (LCLHN) delivers a comprehensive range of in-hospital, aged care, disability, mental health and urgent care services to the Limestone Coast community. 

There are 6 public hospitals, 6 residential aged care facilities, an innovative urgent care site and other health sites located across the region. In-home and community-based services, including community aged care, are provided under the banner of Country Health Connect. 

There are almost 1500 staff across the region, providing services to over 68,000 people in the Limestone Coast, as well as residents from Western Victoria, covering a geographical area of 21,329 square kilometres, and taking in the south-east corner of South Australia.

The LCLHN was established through a Machinery of Government change effective from 1 July 2019, from this date six new regional LHNs replaced Country Health SA Local Health Network. To access data published for reporting periods prior to 2019-20, please see https://data.sa.gov.au/data/dataset/country-health-sa-local-health-network",dataset,eng,Creative Commons Attribution,active,Linked,annual,/data/dataset/27e3f483-df23-4485-8c51-13806275735a,2020-09-08T00:46:59.395037,2025-12-24T04:03:26.504448,dataandreportingservices@sa.gov.au,,2019-07-01,2021-06-30,South Australia,Government of South Australia,data.sa.gov.au,SA Health,"Annual Report, Government, Limestone Coast Local Health Network, SA Health",government-reporting-and-policy
