South Australian climate projections (NARCliM 1.5),"Climate projections for South Australia based on data from the New South Wales and Australian Regional Climate Modelling project (NARCliM 1.5) and intended for use in planning and risk assessments.

Projections are provided for multiple temperature, rainfall and extreme temperatures variables, five time periods (baseline (1985-2005), 2020-2039, 2040-2059, 2060-2079 and 2080-2099) and two Representative Concentration Pathways (RCPs; RCP 4.5 and RCP 8.5).  Projections are provided annually, as well as seasonally for temperature and rainfall variables.",dataset,eng,Creative Commons Attribution,active,Linked,as required,/data/dataset/8adaea04-c29d-4f64-9128-f851262b4cf0,2023-11-21T00:04:11.464832,2023-11-29T07:06:19.598264,blair.pellegrino@sa.gov.au,,1985-01-01,2099-12-31,SA0062407: South Australia,Government of South Australia,data.sa.gov.au,Department for Environment and Water,"Climate, Climate change",water-energy-resources-environment-and-science
