Student attendance by year level,"Student attendance during semester 1 in SA Government schools by year level. Data represents attendance rates for semester 1 of each year from 2012.

Important notes:

•	Attendance rate = (number of days attending school / number of days enrolled) x 100.

•	Semester 1 Attendance rates are only calculated for full time students who were enrolled or left during Semester 1.

•	Both whole day and part day absences are counted. 

•	Attendance data is not collected from schools 1717 Watarru Anangu School (non operational), 849 Open Access College, 810 Thebarton Senior College , 583 Marden Senior College, 1012 Northern Adelaide Senior College and 195 Youth Education Centre.

•	Attendance rates in 2020 are lower than anticipated due to Covid-19 lockdowns.
",dataset,eng,Creative Commons Attribution,active,Linked,annual,/data/dataset/e0c32792-6417-4e51-9f94-9cea8897f13c,2018-05-11T03:36:16.005976,2023-11-21T02:30:58.780974,Education.DataReportingAnalytics@sa.gov.au ,Semester 1 rate by year,2012-03-01,2023-07-31,South Australia,Government of South Australia,data.sa.gov.au,Department for Education,"attendance, education, government, schools, students",education-skills-and-learning
