Women’s Suffrage Petition 1894 (South Australia),"On 23 August 1894 George Hawker, member for North Adelaide, presented to the South Australian House of Assembly a petition in favour of women’s suffrage. It was signed by approximately 11,600 men and women. Members of the Women’s Suffrage League, Woman’s Christian Temperance Union, and the Working Women’s Trade Union were primarily responsible for collecting the signatures from metropolitan and country areas.",dataset,English,Other (Open),active,Hosted,asRequired,/data/dataset/3f6fab54-8cc8-4732-9c1e-fb3f73df53b0,2019-04-04T01:50:27.805462,2019-04-10T07:44:25.748567,webmaster@history.sa.gov.au,,1894-01-01,,South Australia,Government of South Australia,data.sa.gov.au,History Trust of South Australia,"petitions, suffrage, suffrage125",arts-culture-history
