Yorke and Northern Local Health Network (YNLHN),"Yorke and Northern Local Health Network (YNLHN) manage the delivery of public hospital services and other community-based health services as determined by the state government for the Yorke and Northern community. The YNLHN provide health care access to approximately 77,000 people within the Yorke Peninsula, Southern Flinders and the Lower and Mid North areas of South Australia.
We consist of 16 regional hospitals, 6 community health sites, and 15 mixed state and commonwealth funded residential aged care facilities. The Yorke and Northern community have access to a wide range of health care services including emergency care, acute inpatient treatment, surgical, maternal and neonatal, renal dialysis, medium-low risk chemotherapy, residential aged care, outpatient services, and mental health services.
As from 1 July 2019, the State Government established 10 Local Health Networks (LHNs), each with its own Governing Board. From this date, six new regional LHNs replaced Country Health SA Local Health Network. To access data published for reporting periods before 2019-20, please visit https://data.sa.gov.au/data/dataset/country-health-sa-local-health-network
